Interface HlaHLAobjectRootManagerListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HlaHLAobjectRootManagerListener.Adapter
    public interface HlaHLAobjectRootManagerListener
    Listener for changes of HlaHLAobjectRoot instances.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      static class  HlaHLAobjectRootManagerListener.Adapter
      An abstract adapter class that implements the HlaHLAobjectRootManagerListener interface with empty methods.

    • Method Detail

      • hlaHLAobjectRootDiscovered

        void hlaHLAobjectRootDiscovered​(HlaHLAobjectRoot hLAobjectRoot,
                                HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a new HlaHLAobjectRoot instance is discovered. A discovered instance is initially within interest.
        Parameters:
        hLAobjectRoot - the object which is discovered
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaHLAobjectRootInitialized

        void hlaHLAobjectRootInitialized​(HlaHLAobjectRoot hLAobjectRoot,
                                 HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                                 HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaHLAobjectRoot instance is initialized. An instance is initialized when it has been discovered and all attribute marked with initialized has a value.
        Parameters:
        hLAobjectRoot - the object which is initialized
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated

      • hlaHLAobjectRootInInterest

        void hlaHLAobjectRootInInterest​(HlaHLAobjectRoot hLAobjectRoot,
                                HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaHLAobjectRoot instance comes within interest. A discovered instance is initially within interest, so this will not be called at the time of discovery.
        Parameters:
        hLAobjectRoot - the object which has come into interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaHLAobjectRootOutOfInterest

        void hlaHLAobjectRootOutOfInterest​(HlaHLAobjectRoot hLAobjectRoot,
                                   HlaTimeStamp timeStamp)
        This method is called when a HlaHLAobjectRoot instance goes out of interest.
        Parameters:
        hLAobjectRoot - the object which has gone out of interest
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated

      • hlaHLAobjectRootDeleted

        void hlaHLAobjectRootDeleted​(HlaHLAobjectRoot hLAobjectRoot,
                             HlaTimeStamp timeStamp,
                             HlaLogicalTime logicalTime)
        This method is called when a HlaHLAobjectRoot instance is deleted.
        Parameters:
        hLAobjectRoot - the object which is deleted
        timeStamp - the time when the update was initiated
        logicalTime - the logical time when the update was initiated
